<span class="displaytext"><i>as polls close in the final two contests, (PARTY NAME) leaders from across the country pledge their votes to (candidate last)</i> <p>chicago, il - with polls now closed in the final two contest of this historic race for the (PARTY NAME) nomination, 26.5 superdelegates pledged their votes for (candidate full) at the (PARTY NAME) national convention in denver. the superdelegates hail from every region of the country and every level of the (PARTY NAME) party leadership. </p><p>arizona </p><p>congresswoman gabrielle giffords said: </p><p>"now that all primaries and caucuses have concluded, i am enthusiastically endorsing senator (candidate full) as the (PARTY NAME) nominee for president of the united states. since the outset of this historic race for the white house, i have been impressed by the intellect and patriotism of both senator (candidate full) and senator (candidate full). they have demonstrated the passion and wisdom to move our nation towards a brighter future. i respect and admire both of them. </p><p>"every state has had a chance to vote and (candidate full) has emerged with more support. in becoming a delegate for him, i recognize his inspiring and thoughtful leadership that brought him to the finish line. i am proud to join governor janet napolitano and millions of voters throughout the country in supporting (candidate full) as the next president of the united states. i agree with his policy priorities and his commitment to create a cooperative and bipartisan era in american politics. in states large and small, (candidate full) has shared his hope, optimism, and vision of what is possible. americans from all walks of life see in him someone who can truly change our nation. i do as well." </p><p>arizona (PARTY NAME) party chair don bivens said: </p><p>"now that our historic season of caucuses and primaries is behind us, it is time for each superdelegate to choose between two outstanding candidates. for me, that choice is senato